data.reasoningText:
This is the same error - `DateTime` not found. This is strange because `System` should be implicitly imported. Let me check if implicit usings is disabled or if there's something else going on. Let me look at line 11 more carefully.

Actually looking at the full file:
```csharp
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;
class AppDbContext : DbContext
{
    public DbSet<Order> Orders => Set<Order>();
    protected override void OnModelCreating(ModelBuilder modelBuilder)
    {
        modelBuilder.Entity<Order>().HasData(
            new Order { Id = 1, CreatedAt = new DateTime(2024, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Utc) });
    }
}
class Order { public int Id { get; set; } public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; } }
```

The `DateTime` error is appearing in the `Order` class property definition. Implicit usings should be enabled by default for .NET 6+, so maybe the targeting pack for net9.0 isn't installed on this system.

